Sentencas: As the cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), A-site deficient SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (x = 1.9-2.0) (SxFM) materials have been successfully synthesized using the sol-gel combustion method.
Titulo: The characteristic of strontium-site deficient perovskites SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ (x=1.9-2.0) as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: In the perovskite structure of these oxides, the unit cell varies from pseudocubic to cubic with increasing deficiency.
Titulo: The characteristic of strontium-site deficient perovskites SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ (x=1.9-2.0) as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient of SxFM has also been measured and compared with that of Scandium-stabilized zirconium (ScSZ) electrolyte.
Titulo: The characteristic of strontium-site deficient perovskites SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ (x=1.9-2.0) as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) results indicate that the Sr-deficiency has changed the proportion of Fe2+/Fe3+ and Mo6+/Mo5+ ratios, which directly influences the conductivity of SxFM materials.
Titulo: The characteristic of strontium-site deficient perovskites SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ (x=1.9-2.0) as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: S1.950FM possesses the largest electrical conductivity and the lowest polarization resistance (R-p) among all the samples.
Titulo: The characteristic of strontium-site deficient perovskites SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ (x=1.9-2.0) as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of a single cell with the S1.950FM cathode reaches 1083 mW cm(-2), and the area specific resistance value is 0.17 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. These results indicate that the A-site deficiency could promote the electrochemical performance of SFM materials as cathodes for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: The characteristic of strontium-site deficient perovskites SrxFe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ (x=1.9-2.0) as intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathodes
